<td>
<a name="PQN303919"></a>
<br>
<span class="headline">GameSpy Press Release</span><br>
<span class="byline">7/6/01, 16:14 PST | <a href="mailto:aracnakat@rpgplanet.com">Aracnakat</a></span><br><br>
<span class="newsitem">GameSpy.net in June: Ten Titles Ship with GameSpy Tech<br><br>
GameSpy Industries Helps Developers and Publishers Save Time and Money
GameSpy Industries is proud to announce that June 2001 was an unprecedented
month for its GameSpy.net business division, with 10 titles shipping with
GameSpy.net technology powering the games' multiplayer experience and
backend systems.<br><br>
GameSpy.net allows developers and publishers to save tons of man hours and
testing time by "not reinventing the wheel," and using the GameSpy.net
Toolkits. The GameSpy.net Toolkits offer a full package of cross-platform,
technical game development solutions, allowing developers to focus on
building cooler, more profitable games in less time.<br><br>
The following titles, all featuring GameSpy.net technology, shipped in June:<br><br>
	*	Startopia from Eidos Interactive / Mucky Foot <br>
	*	Deep Space Nine: Dominion Wars from Simon and Schuster
Interactive / Gizmo Games <br>
	*	Rules of the Game from Infogrames / Random Games <br>
	*	Operation Flashpoint from Codemasters / Bohemia Interactive <br>
	*	Independence War 2 (European release) from Infogrames /
Particle Systems<br> 
	*	Legends of Might and Magic from 3DO / New World Computing <br>
	*	Gangsters 2 from Eidos Interactive / Hothouse Creations <br>
	*	Baldur's Gate 2: Throne of Bhaal from Interplay / Bioware <br>
	*	Starfleet Command: Orion Pirates from Interplay / Taldren <br>
	*	Z: Steel Soldiers from EON Digital / Bitmap Brothers <br><br>

Legends of Might and Magic, Independence War 2, and Startopia all made
extensive use of GameSpy.net's In-Game Server Browser and In-Game
Matchmaking Toolkits, tightly integrating the multiplayer experience with
the game's user interface. Starfleet Command: Orion Pirates uses the
GameSpy.net CDKey Validation Toolkit, In-Game Chat Toolkit and the In-Game
Server Browsing Toolkit. 
<br><br>
In addition, most of the titles listed above will come bundled with GameSpy
Arcade, the leading multiplayer gaming environment, offering customers a
complete gaming community right out of the box.
<br><br>
Operation Flashpoint particularly enjoyed great success, showing the busiest
lobby of any newly launched title in GameSpy Arcade's history, despite a
limited worldwide release. This title is expected to his the stores in
September in the US.
<br><br>
For more information on how developers and publishers can get started using
the low-cost GameSpy.net tools, please check out <a href="http://www.gamespy.net">www.gamespy.net</a>.</span><br><br>
</td>
<td width="10"><img src="/images/clear.gif" width=10 height=1 border="0"></td>
</tr>
<!-- /News Item Row --><tr>
<td width="33"><img src="/images/clear.gif" width=33 height=1 border="0"></td>
<td>
<a name="PQN303504"></a>
<br>
<span class="headline">Character Transfer Service Announced</span><br>
<span class="byline">7/6/01, 7:50 PST | <a href="mailto:kwill@rpgplanet.com">Kwill</a></span><br><br>
<span class="newsitem">Verant has introduced the opportunity to transfer characters from accounts and from server to server:<blockquote>Due to the many requests to transfer characters from account to account, or server to server, we have
                               implemented a value added service and have enacted a new policy to meet these requests. If you
                               desire to transfer a character or characters from your primary account to your secondary account, or
                               wish to transfer to a different server during non server split opportunities, the following service is
                               offered. This is a value added service which requires a fee that can be billed to your credit card.<br><br>

                               This service to move your character(s) will be offered temporarily. This service may end at any time
                               without prior notification.</blockquote>
One stipulation of the transfer opportunity is worth noting:<blockquote>When moving characters
                                    between accounts, billing information must be identical on both accounts and you
                                    must be the original owner of both accounts. ...attempting to transfer
                                    characters from another person's account or to or from an account purchased by or
                                    for you or given to you where you are not the original registered user of that
                                    account, the characters will not be moved, your request will not be processed or
                                    approved and your account(s) will be subject to review and appropriate disciplinary
                                    action taken.</blockquote>
The basic fee to move one character  is $50.  Moved characters are stripped of all equipment and cash.  To read all the conditions of this offer and to find the request form, <a href="https://store.station.sony.com/eq_char_moves/index.jsp" target="_top">click here to go to the Sony site.</a><br><br>
<b>What do you think of this new policy? We'd love to hear from you in the <a href="http://www.forumplanet.com/PlanetEverQuest/topic.asp?fid=2068&tid=250828">Discussion Forum</a>.</b></span><br><br>
</td>
<td width="10"><img src="/images/clear.gif" width=10 height=1 border="0"></td>
</tr>
