<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr>
<td width="33"><img src="/images/clear.gif" width=33 height=1 border="0"></td>
<td>
<a name="PQN303243"></a>
<br>
<span class="headline">Cleric Gladiator Battle</span><br>
<span class="byline">7/5/01, 8:13 PST | <a href="mailto:kwill@rpgplanet.com">Kwill</a></span><br><br>
<span class="newsitem">Is your favorite cleric really as good as you think they are?  Find out when they are assigned a GM Gladiator to fight for them in this unique Best of the Best Competition!  The contest is for clerics level 54 and up.  Here are the rules:<blockquote>

Each cleric will have a Gladiator assigned to them as a teammate. The object for the Cleric is
                        to kill the opposing Cleric or the opposing Cleric's Gladiator. The Clerics may engage the
                        opposing Gladiator with spells, but may not melee the Gladiator at any time. The Cleric may
                        engage the opposing Cleric with spells or melee anytime after the fight command is issued.<br><br>

                        Each Gladiator will have identical equipment, stats and skills, and will be played by a
                        representative of the Events Staff.<br><br>Immediately before the buffing session the Gladiators will stand in the center of the combat
                        area. They will use auto attack when the fight command is issued by the Events Staff and
                        continue to do so until dispatched by the opposing Gladiator or Cleric. The Gladiator will not
                        move, unless spells cast on them or combat forces them out of combat range. If the Gladiator
                        is forced out of combat range they will immediately move forward to return to combat range.<br><br>

The following spells may not be cast on the opposing cleric's Gladiator at any time: any form
                        of Fear,  Blind,  Death Pact, Divine Intervention or Unswerving Hammer of Faith.<br><br>There is no entry fee for this event and the only prizes will be titles awarded to the winners. Title for winning at the server level will be the
                     level 51 title for Cleric "the Vicar". The title for the 3 runners up on Test Server Finals will be the level 56 title "the Templar". The grand
                     champion of the Test Server Finals shall have the level 60 title given to him on his own server "the High Priest".
</blockquote>
The dates are July 9th through July 26th on Live Servers, times will be posted at least 48 hours in
                        advance. The final is on the Test Server July 28 at Noon. All possible servers will be
                        represented.<br><br>Check out all the rules 
<a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/hht/events/index.jsp" target="_top">at the Events board on Sony's Harpys Head Tavern.</a></span><br><br>
</td>
<td width="10"><img src="/images/clear.gif" width=10 height=1 border="0"></td>
</tr>
<!-- /News Item Row --><tr>
<td width="33"><img src="/images/clear.gif" width=33 height=1 border="0"></td>
<td>
<a name="PQN303241"></a>
<br>
<span class="headline">No New Armor Color</span><br>
<span class="byline">7/5/01, 7:59 PST | <a href="mailto:kwill@rpgplanet.com">Kwill</a></span><br><br>
<span class="newsitem">Some players have been writing to Absor on the Sony Boards and asking for changes in tint or color to armor so it looks as good as the stats say it is.  Absor is very clear on this:<blockquote>We're not going to revamp every piece of armor in the game to meet the desires of a few people just so we can
                          upset other people that liked the way they looked already. In a few rare cases we've seen some changes that
                          seem to make sense. But we are not going to go back and add this graphic to that sword or that color to your
                          favorite piece of armor…<br><br>

                          We certainly understand the desire to have armor that looks the way you want it to look. If you want a different
                          look, there are plenty of other armors or items to use that look different. And no matter what we change to please
                          one person or group, someone else isn't going to like the change. It's not worth our time to annoy one group to
                          please another.</blockquote>So there you have it--if you have really l337 armor that  looks like it came off a level 30 mob, you just have to bask in your secret uberness...or get different armor if you want to look as good as you feel.
</span><br><br>
</td>
<td width="10"><img src="/images/clear.gif" width=10 height=1 border="0"></td>
</tr>
<!-- /News Item Row --></table>
