<span class="headline">Faction Fixes</span><br>
<span class="byline">7/2/01, 9:05 PST | <a href="mailto:kwill@rpgplanet.com">Kwill</a></span><br><br>
<span class="newsitem">For the emergency patch last week, VI fixed three things, one of which you may have already noticed:<br><br>--There is now a message that will let you know when you can no longer gain or lose faction with a certain group.
                          It will say:

                          your faction standing with <faction name> could not possibly get any worse,

                          or

                          your faction standing with <faction name> could not possibly get any better;<br><br>--NPCs do not hate pets as much as they had been before the patch;<br><br>--Fixed a bug that made it impossible to raise some factions.  However, Absor does point out that some factions that cannot be raised because there is no way to raise them, which is intentional.


</span><br><br>
</td>
